00:18:26,340 --> 00:18:32,080
 Hopefully this modern parable of religious Ron

262
00:18:32,080 --> 00:18:35,160
 and lowlife Larry will help us, you and me,

263
00:18:35,160 --> 00:18:40,200
 to enter the worship services here at the Vine

264
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:44,160
 with a desire to primarily focus on three things.

265
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:49,120
 Firstly, the goodness and the greatness of God.

266
00:18:49,120 --> 00:18:53,120
 Secondly, to genuinely worship him

267
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:57,620
 by focusing primarily upon your spiritual needs.

268
00:18:57,620 --> 00:19:02,280
 And thirdly, to offer your life,

269
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:05,320
 to serve him in the ways that bear witness

270
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:08,320
 of his love to others in specific ways.

271
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,440
 In the original parable of the Pharisee

272
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:17,020
 and the tax collector, Jesus said,

273
00:19:17,020 --> 00:19:21,120
 there are two attitudes that people

274
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,560
 generally display in worship.

275
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:28,880
 Number one, I'm proud of my goodness.

276
00:19:28,880 --> 00:19:35,440
 Pride loves to use the personal pronouns I and me.

277
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:39,320
 It seldom omits a need.

278
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:42,740
 It does not focus on the needs of others.

279
00:19:42,740 --> 00:19:50,720
 Or secondly, I desperately need God's mercy.

280
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:55,760
 I've got a question for you.

281
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:58,520
 Which of these two attitudes,

282
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:02,480
 which of these two attitudes best describes your spirit

283
00:20:02,480 --> 00:20:04,740
 as you enter church on a Sunday morning?

284
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:10,300
 Before I finish, I wanna push this a stage further

285
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:11,140
 if you don't mind.

286
00:20:11,140 --> 00:20:14,220
 I wanna get really personal.

287
00:20:14,220 --> 00:20:17,620
 I wanna give you a question.

288
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:24,540
 If you were to die tonight and stand before the Holy God,

289
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:30,980
 on what basis would you seek entrance

290
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:32,820
 into heaven?

291
00:20:32,820 --> 00:20:37,220
 Think about it, I'm gonna say it again.

292
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:43,620
 If you were to die tonight and stand before the Holy God,

293
00:20:43,620 --> 00:20:51,340
 on what basis would you seek entrance into heaven?

294
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:58,460
 I mentioned earlier the parable of the persistent widow

295
00:20:58,460 --> 00:21:00,220
 or the ungodly widow.

296
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:02,940
 The parable of the persistent widow or the unjust judge

297
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:04,380
 that preceded this parable.

298
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:06,980
 It ends with the question.

299
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:09,580
 However, when the Son of Man comes,

300
00:21:09,580 --> 00:21:13,480
 will he find faith on the earth?

301
00:21:13,480 --> 00:21:16,400
 Since now we're getting very serious,

302
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:18,760
 we're talking about our eternal destinies.

303
00:21:18,760 --> 00:21:23,260
 I cannot think of anything more important

304
00:21:23,260 --> 00:21:27,860
 for us to hear the truth of Jesus' message in this parable.

305
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:32,460
 You see, if we were to go out from here today

306
00:21:32,460 --> 00:21:36,420
 and ask people in Yoho Mall,

307
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:39,340
 even those who are regular church goers,

308
00:21:39,340 --> 00:21:41,640
 are you sure of your eternal destiny

309
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,540
 that you'll go to heaven when you die?

310
00:21:43,540 --> 00:21:47,700
 I guarantee that the prevalent answer would be,

311
00:21:47,700 --> 00:21:49,320
 no, I'm not sure.

312
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:55,660
 If we probe a little bit further and ask them why

313
00:21:55,660 --> 00:21:56,780
 they were not sure.

314
00:21:57,740 --> 00:22:01,060
 We'd probably hear things like,

315
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:04,020
 I'm not sure I'm good enough.

316
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:11,300
 Reinforcing a widely held belief that somehow,

317
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:15,420
 somehow our good deeds will be measured up

318
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:19,740
 against our bad ones on some kind of spiritual scorecard.

319
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:22,500
 Salvation by KPIs, you might say.

320
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:26,980
 That we somehow need to earn our way into heaven

321
00:22:26,980 --> 00:22:28,220
 by being good.

322
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:34,440
 Even though we know we are just not able to achieve this.

323
00:22:34,440 --> 00:22:41,780
 The ultimate difficulty that any human being

324
00:22:41,780 --> 00:22:43,300
 will encounter is this.

325
00:22:43,300 --> 00:22:49,420
 How can any unjust person in the presence of a just God

326
00:22:49,420 --> 00:22:54,940
 stand at the last judgment?

327
00:22:54,940 --> 00:22:58,280
 (congregation laughing)

328
00:22:58,280 --> 00:23:04,460
 The only way, the only way we can stand

329
00:23:04,460 --> 00:23:07,860
 is to be justified.

330
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:12,720
 To be declared just.

331
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:17,160
 And when we say that justification is by faith alone,

332
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,260
 that is simple shorthand for justification

333
00:23:20,260 --> 00:23:21,940
 by Jesus Christ alone.

334
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:27,500
 Faith is the sole instrument by which we can grab hold

335
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:31,180
 of Christ and his justice is transferred to us.

336
00:23:31,180 --> 00:23:38,180
 God imputes or counts the righteousness of Jesus

337
00:23:38,180 --> 00:23:40,920
 to those who put their trust in him.

338
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:45,260
 But I tell you today,

339
00:23:45,260 --> 00:23:49,780
 if you trust in yourself,

340
00:23:49,780 --> 00:23:53,620
 you stand by yourself.

341
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:59,620
 The only way you will ever stand before a just

342
00:23:59,620 --> 00:24:03,500
 and holy God is as one clothed in the righteousness

343
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:04,340
 of Christ.

344
00:24:04,340 --> 00:24:07,820
 You add nothing to it.

345
00:24:07,820 --> 00:24:13,820
 Jesus ended this little parable by saying,

346
00:24:13,820 --> 00:24:17,700
 I tell you that this man, the tax collector,

347
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:21,340
 went home justified before God.

348
00:24:22,740 --> 00:24:25,620
 The man couldn't even look up to heaven.

349
00:24:25,620 --> 00:24:30,780
 He couldn't get near to the holy of holies,

350
00:24:30,780 --> 00:24:34,940
 could only beat his chest and repent in sin,

351
00:24:34,940 --> 00:24:38,020
 plead for the mercy of God and throw himself

352
00:24:38,020 --> 00:24:39,740
 at the mercy of the court.

353
00:24:39,740 --> 00:24:47,260
 He walked out the door and went home justified.

354
00:24:50,580 --> 00:24:55,580
 My friends, do not leave here today

355
00:24:55,580 --> 00:25:02,580
 until you tell the Lord God almighty that you are a sinner

356
00:25:02,580 --> 00:25:08,100
 and cannot stand apart from his mercy and grace.

357
00:25:08,100 --> 00:25:13,300
 If you throw yourself and your soul to him

358
00:25:13,300 --> 00:25:15,900
 and his mercy clinging to Christ,

359
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:19,380
 you will go home justified.

360
00:25:19,740 --> 00:25:24,740
 Jesus said of the spiritual man, the Pharisee,

361
00:25:24,740 --> 00:25:32,060
 the one who came so close, so close to the holy place,

362
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:38,420
 the tax collector went home justified rather than the other.

363
00:25:38,420 --> 00:25:45,900
 The Pharisee went home that day and he continued to tithe

364
00:25:45,900 --> 00:25:47,540
 and he continued to fast.

365
00:25:49,180 --> 00:25:53,340
 But he remained an unjustified person.

366
00:25:53,340 --> 00:26:00,100
 If you were to die tonight and stand before God

367
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:04,980
 and God said to you, why should I let you into my heaven?

368
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:07,500
 What would you say?

369
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:15,260
 I hope you would say, because of Jesus.

370
00:26:17,340 --> 00:26:22,340
 Because he's my only hope, I put my trust in him.

371
00:26:22,340 --> 00:26:27,500
 Everything else is sinking sand.

372
00:26:27,500 --> 00:26:31,740
 Then he will look at you.

373
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:38,500
 He'll say, please come in.

374
00:26:38,500 --> 00:26:41,580
 My son is already here.

375
00:26:41,580 --> 00:26:44,220
 He's prepared a place for you

376
00:26:46,380 --> 00:26:51,380
 that you might bask in his glory now and forevermore.

377
00:26:51,380 --> 00:26:58,540
 Let's close our eyes and ask the worship band to come back.

378
00:26:58,540 --> 00:27:09,660
 We're gonna be singing that song, Come to the Altar, again.

379
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:14,540
 I joked about it before I preached the sermon.

380
00:27:14,540 --> 00:27:17,020
 I think the song had already done my sermon for me.

381
00:27:17,020 --> 00:27:18,020
 It's a middle song.

382
00:27:18,020 --> 00:27:23,180
 I want you to use that song

383
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:29,980
 to come back to the altar on your knees before Jesus

384
00:27:29,980 --> 00:27:33,180
 where the place is forgiveness.

385
00:27:33,180 --> 00:27:38,700
 But I wanna give an opportunity right here and now

386
00:27:38,700 --> 00:27:43,420
 for anyone who's here today, a friend may have brought you.

387
00:27:44,260 --> 00:27:46,620
 You may have been coming to church for a while,

388
00:27:46,620 --> 00:27:48,820
 but you've never said,

389
00:27:48,820 --> 00:27:52,060
 Jesus, I want you to be the savior of my life.

390
00:27:52,060 --> 00:27:57,300
 You come here, you love the music,

391
00:27:57,300 --> 00:27:59,300
 you love the fellowship, the friendship,

392
00:27:59,300 --> 00:28:06,180
 but you've never asked Jesus to be the savior of your life,

393
00:28:06,180 --> 00:28:10,220
 trust in him for your salvation.

394
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:13,380
 Can I tell you it's the only way?

395
00:28:13,380 --> 00:28:19,100
 Don't go home from this sermon

396
00:28:19,100 --> 00:28:21,180
 and read the Bible from cover to cover,

397
00:28:21,180 --> 00:28:24,300
 pray for three hours, put on worship music all night

398
00:28:24,300 --> 00:28:28,900
 to try and do things to get close to God.

399
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:30,860
 None of those things are bad by the way,

400
00:28:30,860 --> 00:28:34,980
 but they are if you think that's the way

401
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:37,260
 that you're gonna get right with God.

402
00:28:37,260 --> 00:28:41,460
 The only way today that you are gonna get right with God

403
00:28:41,460 --> 00:28:43,500
 is to be like that tax collector.

404
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:48,140
 Father, I'm a sinner.

405
00:28:48,140 --> 00:28:51,260
 That's not too difficult, we've all sinned.

406
00:28:51,260 --> 00:28:54,620
 We are all sinners.

407
00:28:54,620 --> 00:28:59,620
 Father, I am a sinner, I am in need of your forgiveness.

408
00:28:59,620 --> 00:29:03,500
 And just what every eye is closed

409
00:29:03,500 --> 00:29:05,300
 and please respect this for a moment.

410
00:29:06,340 --> 00:29:07,700
 If there is anyone here

411
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:10,180
 who wants to pray that prayer for themselves,

412
00:29:10,180 --> 00:29:11,900
 who wants to pray that prayer to say,

413
00:29:11,900 --> 00:29:16,900
 Jesus, I'm a sinner, I need you, come into my life.

414
00:29:16,900 --> 00:29:21,980
 I want you to do something very, very simple,

415
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:23,500
 just what every eye is closed.

416
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:27,100
 I'd love to pray for you.

417
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:31,340
 And just to know who I'm praying for, if that's you,

418
00:29:31,340 --> 00:29:34,660
 I'm gonna ask you one simple thing.

419
00:29:35,020 --> 00:29:40,020
 Just to pop up your hand, raise your hands, thank you.

420
00:29:40,020 --> 00:29:41,740
 Raise your hand.

421
00:29:41,740 --> 00:29:44,340
 This is only if you wanna pray this prayer, right?

422
00:29:44,340 --> 00:29:48,060
 I'm not asking everyone to raise their hands,

423
00:29:48,060 --> 00:29:51,380
 but if that's you, you want to ask Jesus

424
00:29:51,380 --> 00:29:53,100
 into your life this morning.

425
00:29:53,100 --> 00:29:55,780
 You want to say sorry for the things I've done wrong.

426
00:29:55,780 --> 00:30:02,660
 If you do that, you go home justified.

427
00:30:02,700 --> 00:30:05,500
 If you die tonight or if you die in 40 years time,

428
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:14,060
 God will have heard your prayer.

429
00:30:14,060 --> 00:30:17,460
 So maybe as a church, we could pray this all together

430
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:19,620
 just for the people who put their hands up.

431
00:30:19,620 --> 00:30:25,500
 Church, repeat after me, Father God,

432
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:28,140
 I come before you now,

433
00:30:30,140 --> 00:30:31,460
 I come before you now,

434
00:30:31,460 --> 00:30:36,580
 I recognize that I am a sinner.

435
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:39,660
 I'm in need of forgiveness.

436
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:43,260
 Jesus, I believe you're the Son of God.

437
00:30:43,260 --> 00:30:46,260
 You died for me.

438
00:30:46,260 --> 00:30:51,140
 Jesus, forgive my sins.

439
00:30:51,140 --> 00:30:54,580
 Come into my life, fill me with your spirit

440
00:30:54,580 --> 00:30:57,900
 and help me to live a life for you.

441
00:30:58,060 --> 00:30:59,700
 I pray this now in Jesus' name.

442
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:02,540
 Amen.

443
00:31:02,540 --> 00:31:05,140
 Let's welcome those who's prayed that for the first time.

444
00:31:05,140 --> 00:31:11,780
 And church, we all have an opportunity now.

445
00:31:11,780 --> 00:31:15,060
 Don't be thinking now what you're gonna have for lunch,

446
00:31:15,060 --> 00:31:16,180
 where are you gonna go?

447
00:31:16,180 --> 00:31:19,060
 Come to the altar.

448
00:31:19,060 --> 00:31:22,540
 Look at these words as you sing them.

